kpi_info.title: period_duration
kpi_info.use: Duration of the measurement period in minutes.

kpi_info.title: PS_SESSION_REQ_UL
kpi_info.use: The number of packet call resource allocation attempts caused by uplink capacity request. UPDATED:When uplink capacity request is received by Layer-3 telecom entity from a UE for which RNC resources for packet call do not exist (e.g. in Cell-PCH state).

kpi_info.title: PS_SESSION_REQ_DL
kpi_info.use: The number of packet call resource allocation attempts caused by downlink capacity request. UPDATED:When downlink capacity request is received by Layer-3 telecom entity from the upper protocol layer for which RNC resources for packet call do not exist (e.g. in Cell-PCH state).

kpi_info.title: PS_SESSION_REQ_OTHER
kpi_info.use: The number of packet call resource allocation attempts not caused by uplink or downlink capacity request. UPDATED:When a packet call resource allocation attempt is triggered by other than uplink or downlink capacity request, e.g., when RANAP: Relocation Request is received during incoming Inter-RNC HHO or SRNC Relocation.

kpi_info.title: PS_ATT_HSDSCH_EDCH_INT
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH/E-DCH packet call attempts for interactive traffic class. UPDATED:When the UE-specific packet scheduler attempts to allocate an HS-DSCH/E-DCH transport channel for the NRT RAB, and there are no dedicated/shared channels that are already allocated for the RAB. This counter is updated if the UE is HSUPA capable, even if HSUPA would not be enabled in the cell.

kpi_info.title: IUB_DELAY_CC_DELAY_IND
kpi_info.use: The number of "Congestion Indication control frame - delay build-up" sent to BTS due to Iub delay detected by Frame protocol. UPDATED:When the RNC Frame Protocol entity sends "Congestion Indication control frame - delay build-up" indication to the base station and the indication was triggered by congestion detected by Frame Protocol entity. This counter is updated for all cells in the UEs E-DCH active set controlled by the base station for which the Congestion Indication was sent. The counter is not updated for E-DCH soft handover branches controlled by base stations whose Iub interface is not congested, because Congestion Indication is not sent to them.

kpi_info.title: SUCC_EDCH_FP_BRANCH_SETUP
kpi_info.use: The number of successful E-DCH Iub Frame Protocol branch setups. UPDATED:When a new E-DCH Frame Protocol branch is successfully established in Iub. The counter is not updated when a softer handover branch is added because new FP connection is not created in that case.

kpi_info.title: MISSED_EDCH_FRAMES
kpi_info.use: The number of E-DCH frames that that are not received at all or are discarded due to errors. UPDATED:When an E-DCH FP frame is detected to be missing or discarded as erroneous.

kpi_info.title: DELAYED_EDCH_FRAMES
kpi_info.use: The number of delayed E-DCH FP frames, this includes frames that are delayed over the trigger value used by congestion control algorithm (i.e. delay is above the DelayThresholdMin). UPDATED:When an E-DCH frame is received and detected as delayed over the trigger value used by congestion control algorithm.

kpi_info.title: SUCC_REC_EDCH_FRAMES
kpi_info.use: The number of successfully received E-DCH FP frames, including all other frames than the frames counted as missed or delayed. UPDATED:When an E-DCH frame is received successfully and in time.

UPDATED: When the UE-specific packet scheduler attempts to allocate an HS-DSCH/E-DCH transport channel for the PS Streaming RAB, and there are no dedicated/shared channels that are already allocated for the RAB. This counter is updated if the UE is HSUPA capable, even if HSUPA would not be enabled in the cell.

kpi_info.title: PS_ATT_HSDSCH_DCH_STRE
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH/DCH packet call attempts for the streaming traffic class. UPDATED: When the UE-specific packet scheduler attempts to allocate an HS-DSCH/DCH transport channel for the PS Streaming RAB, and there are no dedicated/shared channels that are already allocated for the RAB. This counter is updated if the UE is HSDPA capable, even if HSDPA would not be enabled in the cell.

kpi_info.title: PS_ATT_DCH_DCH_STRE
kpi_info.use: The number of DCH/DCH packet call attempts for the streaming traffic class. UPDATED: When the UE-specific packet scheduler attempts to allocate a DCH/DCH transport channel for the PS Streaming RAB, and there are no dedicated/shared channels that are already allocated for the RAB.

kpi_info.title: PS_SETUP_FAIL_AC_STRE
kpi_info.use: The number of packet call setup failures due to the admission control for the streaming traffic class. UPDATED:When the PS user plane allocation is rejected by the admission control.

kpi_info.title: PS_SETUP_FAIL_BTS_STRE
kpi_info.use: The number of packet call setup failures due to the BTS for the streaming traffic class. UPDATED: When the PS user plane allocation fails due to the BTS responding with an NBAP: RADIO LINK SETUP FAILURE or an NBAP: RADIO LINK RECONFIGURATION FAILURE message, or not responding at all.

kpi_info.title: PS_SETUP_FAIL_DMCU_STRE
kpi_info.use: The number of packet call setup failures due to the lack of DMCU resources for the streaming traffic class. UPDATED: When the PS user plane allocation fails due to a DMCU resource allocation failure.

kpi_info.title: PS_SETUP_FAIL_TRANS_STRE
kpi_info.use: The number of packet call setup failures due to transport for the streaming traffic class. UPDATED: When the PS user plane allocation fails due to an Iub transport setup failure.

kpi_info.title: PS_SETUP_FAIL_UE_STRE
kpi_info.use: The number of packet call setup failures due to the UE for the streaming traffic class. UPDATED: When the PS user plane allocation fails due to the UE responding with an RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION FAILURE message or not responding at all.

kpi_info.title: PS_SETUP_FAIL_OTHER_STRE
kpi_info.use: The number of packet call setup failures for the streaming traffic class due to other reasons than those covered by the other failure counters. UPDATED: When the PS user plane allocation fails due to any other reason not covered by the other failure counters.

kpi_info.title: HS_E_REQ_HS_E_ALLO_STRE
kpi_info.use: The number of allocations for the HS-DSCH/E-DCH after an HS-DSCH/E-DCH request for the streaming traffic class. UPDATED: When the user's HS-DSCH/E-DCH user plane allocation is successfully completed.

kpi_info.title: HS_E_REQ_HS_D_ALLO_STRE
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH/DCH allocations after an HS-DCSH/E-DCH request for the streaming traffic class. UPDATED: When the user is successfully allocated to the HS-DSCH/DCH user plane and the request was for the HS-DSCH/E-DCH.

kpi_info.title: HS_D_REQ_HS_D_ALLO_STRE
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH/DCH allocations after an HS-DSCH/DCH request for the streaming traffic class. UPDATED: When the user is successfully allocated to the HS-DSCH/DCH user plane and the request was for the HS-DSCH/DCH.

kpi_info.title: HS_E_REQ_D_D_ALLO_STRE
kpi_info.use: The number of DCH/DCH allocations after an HS-DSCH/E-DCH request for the streaming traffic class. UPDATED: When the user is successfully allocated to the DCH/DCH user plane and the request was for the HS-DSCH/E-DCH.

kpi_info.title: HS_D_REQ_D_D_ALLO_STRE
kpi_info.use: The number of DCH/DCH allocations after an HS-DSCH/DCH request for the streaming traffic class. UPDATED: When the user is successfully allocated to the DCH/DCH user plane and the request was for the HS-DSCH/DCH.

kpi_info.title: D_D_REQ_D_D_ALLO_STRE
kpi_info.use: The number of DCH/DCH allocations after a DCH/DCH request for the streaming traffic class. UPDATED: When the user is successfully allocated to the DCH/DCH user plane and the request was for the DCH/DCH.

kpi_info.title: PS_SWI_HS_E_TO_HS_D_STRE
kpi_info.use: The number of packet call channel switches from the HS-DSCH/E-DCH to the HS-DSCH/DCH for the streaming traffic class. UPDATED: When the user's HS-DSCH/E-DCH user plane allocation is switched to the HS-DSCH/DCH.

kpi_info.title: PS_SWI_HS_E_TO_D_D_STRE
kpi_info.use: The number of packet call channel switches from the HS-DSCH/E-DCH to the DCH/DCH (xx/yy) for the streaming traffic class. UPDATED: When the user's HS-DSCH/E-DCH user plane allocation is switched to the DCH/DCH (xx/yy).

kpi_info.title: PS_SWI_HS_D_TO_D_D_STRE
kpi_info.use: The number of packet call channel switches from the HS-DSCH/DCH to the DCH/DCH (xx/yy) for the streaming traffic class. UPDATED: When the user's HS-DSCH/DCH user plane allocation is switched to the DCH/DCH (xx/yy).

kpi_info.title: PS_SWI_HS_D_TO_HS_E_STRE
kpi_info.use: The number of packet call channel switches from the HS-DSCH/DCH to the HS-DSCH/E-DCH for the streaming traffic class. UPDATED: When the user's HS-DSCH/DCH user plane allocation is switched to the HS-DSCH/E-DCH.

kpi_info.title: PS_SWI_D_D_TO_HS_D_STRE
kpi_info.use: The number of packet call channel switches from the DCH/DCH (xx/yy) to the HS-DSCH/DCH for the streaming traffic class. UPDATED: When the user's DCH/DCH (xx/yy) user plane allocation is switched to the HS-DSCH/DCH.

kpi_info.title: PS_SWI_D_D_TO_HS_E_STRE
kpi_info.use: The number of packet call channel switches from the DCH/DCH (xx/yy) to the HS-DSCH/E-DCH for the streaming traffic class. UPDATED: When the user's DCH/DCH (xx/yy) user plane allocation is switched to the HS-DCSH/E-DCH.

kpi_info.title: PS_REL_NORM_HS_E_STRE
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH/E-DCH packet call normal releases for the streaming traffic class. UPDATED: When a packet call is released normally, for example, due to inactivity or an RAB release. The counter is also updated in case of outgoing SRNC relocations, Inter-RNC hard handovers, and Inter-system hard handovers, and due to state transitions to the DCH

kpi_info.title: PS_REL_NORM_HS_D_STRE
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH/DCH packet call normal releases for the streaming traffic class. UPDATED: When a packet call is released normally, for example, due to inactivity or an RAB release. The counter is also updated in case of outgoing SRNC relocations, Inter-RNC hard handovers, and Inter-system hard handovers, and due to state transitions to the DCH

kpi_info.title: PS_REL_NORM_D_D_STRE

The counter is also updated in case of outgoing SRNC relocations, Inter-RNC hard handovers, and Inter-system hard handovers, and due to state transitions to the DCH

kpi_info.title: PS_REL_PRE_EMP_HS_E_STRE
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH/E-DCH packet call releases caused by pre-emption or RT over NRT for the streaming traffic class. UPDATED: When a packet call is released due to pre-emption by a higher priority radio bearer.

kpi_info.title: PS_REL_PRE_EMP_HS_D_STRE
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH/DCH packet call releases caused by pre-emption or RT over NRT for the streaming traffic class. UPDATED:When a packet call is released due to pre-emption by a higher priority radio bearer.

kpi_info.title: PS_REL_PRE_EMP_D_D_STRE
kpi_info.use: The number of DCH/DCH packet call releases caused by pre-emption or RT over NRT for the streaming traffic class. UPDATED: When a packet call is released due to pre-emption by a higher priority radio bearer.

kpi_info.title: PS_REL_RL_FAIL_HS_E_STRE
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH/E-DCH packet call releases caused by radio link failures for the streaming traffic class. UPDATED: When a packet call is released due to a radio link failure, that is, all radio links go out of the sync state during a packet call and thus the dedicated user plane is released.

kpi_info.title: PS_REL_RL_FAIL_HS_D_STRE
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH/DCH packet call releases caused by radio link failures for the streaming traffic class. UPDATED: When a packet call is released due to a radio link failure, that is, all radio links go out of the sync state during a packet call and thus the dedicated user plane is released.

kpi_info.title: PS_REL_RL_FAIL_D_D_STRE
kpi_info.use: The number of DCH/DCH packet call releases caused by radio link failures for the streaming traffic class. UPDATED: When a packet call is released due to a radio link failure, that is, all radio links go out of the sync state during a packet call and thus the dedicated user plane is released.

kpi_info.title: PS_REL_OTH_FAIL_HS_E_STRE
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH/E-DCH packet call releases caused by other failure reasons than a radio link failure for the streaming traffic class. UPDATED: When a packet call is released for some other failure cause than a radio link failure, for example, when the reservation of the DMPG resource does not succeed when switching the HSPA to the DCH, or a DSP runtime error occurs.

kpi_info.use: The number of DCH/DCH allocations after an HS-DCSH/DCH request for the streaming traffic class due to the cell not supporting HSDPA. UPDATED: When the user is successfully allocated to the DCH/DCH user plane and the request was for the HS-DSCH/DCH. The reason for selecting Rel99 was that HSDPA is not enabled in the cell.

kpi_info.title: SUCC_SWI_DCHSDPA_TO_SCHSDPA
kpi_info.use: The number of successful channel switches from DC-HSDPA to single-carrier HSDPA. The counter is updated independently of possible MIMO or DC-HSUPA usage. UPDATED: When the RNC receives RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message from the UE after a successful channel switch from DC-HSDPA to SC-HSDPA.

kpi_info.title: SUCC_SWI_SCHSDPA_TO_DCHSDPA
kpi_info.use: The number of successful channel switches from single-carrier HSDPA to DC-HSDPA. The counter is updated independently of possible MIMO or DC-HSUPA usage. UPDATED: When the RNC receives RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message from the UE after a successful channel switch from SC-HSDPA to DC-HSDPA.

kpi_info.title: RX_PACKETS_DSCP_DL_TCP_ACK
kpi_info.use: The number of received user plane packets from the Iu-PS interface with DSCP marking matching DL TCP ACK indicating low priority traffic in UL. Only traffic transferred over HS-DSCH is included. The counter is updated for the HS-DSCH serving cell. UPDATED: When Iu-PS user plane IP-packet is received from the CN and the inner IP-packet DSCP code matches with that defined by parameter RNC->DSCPStatisticsGroupTCPack.

kpi_info.title: RX_PACKETS_DSCP_INIT_SPI
kpi_info.use: The number of received user plane packets from the Iu-PS interface with DSCP markings that are configured to use initial SPI at BTS scheduler. Only traffic transferred over HS-DSCH is included. The counter is updated for the HS-DSCH serving cell. UPDATED: When Iu-PS user plane IP-packet is received from the CN and it is mapped to the initial SPI. This can happen if the packet does not have DSCP code marking or there is no entry for the used DSCP in the RNC configuration.

kpi_info.title: RX_PACKETS_DSCP_A
kpi_info.use: The number of received user plane packets from the Iu-PS interface with pre-defined DSCP marking A. Only traffic transferred over HS-DSCH is included. The counter is updated for the HS-DSCH serving cell. UPDATED: When Iu-PS user plane IP-packet is received from the CN and the inner IP-packet DSCP code matches with that defined by parameter RNC->DSCPStatisticsGroupA.

kpi_info.title: RX_PACKETS_DSCP_B
kpi_info.use: The number of received user plane packets from the Iu-PS interface with pre-defined DSCP marking B. Only traffic transferred over HS-DSCH is included. The counter is updated for the HS-DSCH serving cell. UPDATED: When Iu-PS user plane IP-packet is received from the CN and the inner IP-packet DSCP code matches with that defined by parameter RNC->DSCPStatisticsGroupB.

kpi_info.title: RX_PACKETS_DSCP_C
kpi_info.use: The number of received user plane packets from the Iu-PS interface with pre-defined DSCP marking C. Only traffic transferred over HS-DSCH is included. The counter is updated for the HS-DSCH serving cell. UPDATED: When Iu-PS user plane IP-packet is received from the CN and the inner IP-packet DSCP code matches with that defined by parameter RNC->DSCPStatisticsGroupC.

kpi_info.title: PS_UP_REL_DUE_CH_SWITCH_FAIL
kpi_info.use: The number of PS NRT user plane reconfigurations to DCH 0/0 because of failed channel type switch. UPDATED: When channel type switch from HSxPA to Rel99 DCH x/y is triggered and for some reason the procedure fails and therefore DCH 0/0 is allocated instead. In multi RAB cases this counter is updated seprately for every RAB.

kpi_info.title: PS_UP_REL_DUE_INACTIVITY
kpi_info.use: The number of PS NRT user plane reconfigurations to DCH 0/0 because of user plane inactivity. UPDATED: When L2 indicates inactivity to L3 which triggers user plane release to DCH 0/0. The original channel type can be HSxPA or Rel99 DCH x/y. Using DCH 0/0 instead of PCH or FACH happens because the UE has got another RAB whose user plane cannot be released, for example CS call.

kpi_info.title: ATT_HSPA_TO_DCH
kpi_info.use: The number of PS NRT reconfiguration attempts from HSxPA to Rel99 DCH x/y. The difference to counter M1022C149 is that M1022C149 covers only the RRC signalling part after the resources are already successfully reserved, but counter M1022C232 covers also the resource reservation attempt. UPDATED: When the RNC initiates resource reservation for channel type switch from HSxPA to Rel99 DCH x/y.

kpi_info.title: SUCC_HSPA_TO_DCH
kpi_info.use: The number of successful PS NRT reconfigurations from HSxPA to Rel99 DCH x/y. Failures in this procedure can indirectly be monitored with M1022C230, but it must be noted that M1022C230 covers only such failures that happened in the resource allocation phase as after such situation switch to DCH 0/0 is performed. UPDATED: When the channel type switch from HSxPA to Rel99 DCH is successful and the UE responds with Radio Bearer Reconfiguration Complete.

kpi_info.title: PS_SETUP_FAIL_AC_UL_NRT
kpi_info.use: The number of packet call setup failures caused by admission control because of uplink power limitation for PS NRT calls. M1022C9 or M1022C10 is also updated along with this counter. UPDATED: When the PS user plane allocation is rejected by the uplink power admission control.

kpi_info.title: PS_SETUP_FAIL_AC_DL_NRT
kpi_info.use: The number of packet call setup failures caused by admission control because of downlink power limitation for PS NRT calls. M1022C9 or M1022C10 is also updated along with this counter. UPDATED: When the PS user plane allocation is rejected by the downlink power admission control.

kpi_info.title: PS_SETUP_FAIL_AC_COD_NRT
kpi_info.use: The number of packet call setup failures caused by admission control because of downlink spreading code congestion. M1022C9 or M1022C10 is also updated along with this counter. UPDATED: When the PS user plane allocation is rejected by the admission control because of downlink spreading code congestion.

kpi_info.title: RLC_RESET_BY_RNC
kpi_info.use: The number of RLC protocol resets triggered by the AM RLC entity of the RNC (AM RLC protocol reset causes and channel type switch/state transition cases).Only PS user plane radio bearers are measured. Updated:When the RNC triggers RLC protocol reset.

kpi_info.title: RLC_RESET_BY_UE
kpi_info.use: The number of RLC protocol resets triggered by the AM RLC entity of the UE (AM RLC protocol reset causes).Only PS user plane radio bearers are measured. Updated:When the UE triggers RLC protocol reset.

kpi_info.title: RLC_DL_SDU_BYTES_RECEIVED
kpi_info.use: The number of DL SDU data bytes received at PDCP/RLC for DL transmission (payload).Only PS user plane radio bearers are measured. Updated:When the RLC protocol entity in the RNC receives user data in the downlink direction.

kpi_info.title: RLC_UL_SDU_BYTES_RECEIVED
kpi_info.use: The number of payload bytes sent to the CN.Only PS user plane radio bearers are measured. Updated:When the RLC protocol entity in the RNC sends uplink user data towards the CN.

kpi_info.title: RLC_DL_SDU_BYTES_DROPPED
kpi_info.use: The number of DL SDU bytes dropped at PDCP/RLC due to lack of memory. Only PS user plane radio bearers are measured. Updated:When DL SDU is dropped in the PDCP/RLC layer in the RNC due to lack of memory.

kpi_info.title: RLC_UL_PDU_DROPPED
kpi_info.use: The number of PDUs dropped at RLC due to LI errors, lack of memory or UL PDUs received outside the receive window.Only PS user plane radio bearers are measured. Updated:When RLC UL PDU is dropped due to erroneous PDU, lack of memory or PDU received outside the receiving window.

kpi_info.title: RLC_DL_PDU_SENT
kpi_info.use: The number of transmitted DL PDUs at RLC, including retransmissions.Only PS user plane radio bearers are measured.Updated:When the RNC RLC entity sends RLC DL PDU towards MAC layer.

kpi_info.title: RLC_DL_PDU_ACKED
kpi_info.use: The number of transmitted PDUs on DL acknowledged by the UE.Only PS user plane radio bearers are measured. Updated:When the UE acknowledges successful reception of RLC DL PDU.Updated: When the UE acknowledges successful reception of RLC DL PDU.

kpi_info.title: RLC_DL_PDU_RETRANSMITTED
kpi_info.use: The number of DL PDUs retransmitted to UE. Retransmissions due to polling are not included but only retransmissions related to lost PDUs.Only PS user plane radio bearers are measured. Updated:When RLC DL PDU is retransmitted.

kpi_info.title: RLC_DL_PDU_DISCARDED
kpi_info.use: The number of DL RLC PDUs discarded due to max retransmissions reached, Move Receiving Window command or discard timer expiry.Only PS user plane radio bearers are measured. Updated:When DL RLC PDU is discarded.

kpi_info.title: RLC_TRANSM_WINDOW_STALL
kpi_info.use: The number of times ACK status PDU failed to update VT(A) when TX window is full causing reset procedure with reason invalid UL status PDU.Only PS user plane radio bearers are measured.Updated: When RLC transmission window stalls triggering RLC reset procedure.

kpi_info.title: period_duration_sum
kpi_info.use: Duration of the measurement period in minutes.
